WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.839 --> 00:00:07.340
[birdsong]

2
00:00:07.382 --> 00:00:09.009
[footsteps approaching]

3
00:00:09.050 --> 00:00:10.510
[man groaning]

4
00:00:10.552 --> 00:00:13.346
[whistling "On to Ashford"]

5
00:00:13.388 --> 00:00:16.433
[Dunk]
You-- you might not
remember him. but. um...

6
00:00:16.474 --> 00:00:19.144
Stay there.
I'm coming back.

7
00:00:19.185 --> 00:00:20.520
[Dunk]
...he was a true knight.

8
00:00:20.562 --> 00:00:22.272
[rooster crowing]

9
00:00:22.272 --> 00:00:25.275
[Dunk]
Uh. different than
other men. Yeah.

10
00:00:25.316 --> 00:00:27.277
[sighs]

11
00:00:27.318 --> 00:00:29.154
He had a peaceable nature.

12
00:00:30.321 --> 00:00:33.033
-Quiet and humble.
-[sighs]

13
00:00:33.074 --> 00:00:35.827
A veteran of a hundred wars.
but an enemy to none.

14
00:00:39.372 --> 00:00:42.042
He always knew
what was expected of him.

15
00:00:42.083 --> 00:00:43.793
Hm.

16
00:00:43.835 --> 00:00:45.295
He never complained.

17
00:00:45.295 --> 00:00:47.213
-[sighs deeply]
-[horse nickering]

18
00:00:47.255 --> 00:00:50.967
Even as he was dying.
he... he just...

19
00:00:51.009 --> 00:00:53.136
[sheep bleating]

20
00:00:53.178 --> 00:00:54.971
He just got on with it.

21
00:00:55.013 --> 00:00:57.015
-[rooster crowing]
-[people chattering]

22
00:00:58.058 --> 00:01:01.061
He-- he meant to be a benefit
to those around him.

23
00:01:03.688 --> 00:01:05.565
It did not make him rich.

24
00:01:05.607 --> 00:01:10.153
He-- he held no lands.
sired no children.

25
00:01:10.195 --> 00:01:11.821
[whistling]

26
00:01:11.821 --> 00:01:14.157
[singing]
♪ Off to Ashford
to see a fair maid ♪

27
00:01:14.199 --> 00:01:16.408
♪ Heigh-ho. heigh-ho ♪

28
00:01:16.451 --> 00:01:19.996
♪ I'll make her my love
and we'll rest in the shade ♪

29
00:01:20.038 --> 00:01:21.914
♪ Heigh-ho. heigh-ho ♪

30
00:01:21.956 --> 00:01:23.166
-Come on. Dunk!
-[horse whinnying]

31
00:01:23.208 --> 00:01:25.085
-[rain pattering]
-[thunder rumbling]

32
00:01:25.126 --> 00:01:27.128
[panting]

33
00:01:29.047 --> 00:01:31.549
[Dunk]
He-- he wanted for nothing
but the open air.

34
00:01:32.509 --> 00:01:33.676
Hey.

35
00:01:33.718 --> 00:01:35.845
And a fire
to warm his feet at.

36
00:01:35.887 --> 00:01:38.098
[cow mooing]

37
00:01:39.307 --> 00:01:40.683
[chuckles]

38
00:01:41.893 --> 00:01:44.229
[both laughing]

39
00:01:44.270 --> 00:01:45.688
His skills as
a warrior were...

40
00:01:45.688 --> 00:01:47.565
[grunting]

41
00:01:47.607 --> 00:01:49.067
...unsung.

42
00:01:49.109 --> 00:01:51.569
but he had a chin
cut from granite.

43
00:01:51.610 --> 00:01:54.697
-Come on.
-And he was
a dogged fighter.

44
00:01:54.697 --> 00:01:56.699
-He just. he kept on coming.
-[shouting]

45
00:01:56.741 --> 00:01:58.743
-[horse chortling]
-[Arlan whistling]

46
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:09.211
♪ I'll steal a sweet kiss
from the point of my blade ♪

47
00:02:09.211 --> 00:02:11.714
♪ Heigh-ho. heigh-ho ♪

48
00:02:13.049 --> 00:02:14.425
[whistling]

49
00:02:14.467 --> 00:02:16.553
Whoa! Whoa!

50
00:02:16.553 --> 00:02:18.555
-[horse neighing]
-[panting]

51
00:02:24.185 --> 00:02:27.272
[Dunk]
House Florent. Ser Arlan
took service in your guard

52
00:02:27.313 --> 00:02:29.232
when your lord father
lost his sight.

53
00:02:29.274 --> 00:02:32.152
♪ I'll make her my love
and we'll rest in the shade ♪

54
00:02:32.192 --> 00:02:34.487
♪ Heigh-ho. heigh-ho ♪

55
00:02:34.529 --> 00:02:36.239
[Dunk]
House Hayford.

56
00:02:36.281 --> 00:02:37.949
Ser Arlan
fought side by side

57
00:02:37.991 --> 00:02:39.826
with your brothers
at the Redgrass.

58
00:02:41.703 --> 00:02:43.788
His squire. his--
his own nephew

59
00:02:43.829 --> 00:02:45.206
was killed in the battle.

60
00:02:47.458 --> 00:02:49.335
House Tyrell...

61
00:02:50.253 --> 00:02:52.422
Ser Arlan often spoke
of his time in your service

62
00:02:52.422 --> 00:02:55.175
as his very finest.

63
00:02:56.384 --> 00:03:00.680
He said it was you. m'lord.
who told him that a hedge knight

64
00:03:00.722 --> 00:03:03.183
was the bridge between lords
and the smallfolk.

65
00:03:04.267 --> 00:03:05.435
[spitting]

66
00:03:08.313 --> 00:03:09.772
I know him not. man.

67
00:03:09.772 --> 00:03:12.275
[people laughing]

68
00:03:12.275 --> 00:03:13.776
Was he a shit knight?

69
00:03:13.818 --> 00:03:15.778
-He was not a shit knight.
-Well. he can't have been

70
00:03:15.778 --> 00:03:18.031
a very good one
if no one remembers him.

71
00:03:18.072 --> 00:03:19.949
Pick up your feet.
come on.

72
00:03:19.949 --> 00:03:21.492
This is undignified. ser.

73
00:03:21.534 --> 00:03:25.121
So. hie back to camp and
leave me be. if it please you.

74
00:03:25.163 --> 00:03:26.998
I would not leave you. ser.

75
00:03:27.040 --> 00:03:29.167
not while you must
suffer your master dying

76
00:03:29.209 --> 00:03:30.793
over and over again.

77
00:03:30.835 --> 00:03:32.629
Though it does not seem
like these lords

78
00:03:32.629 --> 00:03:35.131
-are even listening to you.
-[scoffs]

79
00:03:35.131 --> 00:03:37.634
Nothing I can do about that.

80
00:03:37.634 --> 00:03:40.053
You are a knight
of the realm. ser.

81
00:03:40.094 --> 00:03:41.971
You can say
fuck their permission.

82
00:03:41.971 --> 00:03:44.224
Ride into the lists.
call out Longthorn Tyrell.

83
00:03:44.265 --> 00:03:46.476
and turn his arsehole
into a lance-hole.

84
00:03:48.102 --> 00:03:49.812
That's enough now.

85
00:03:49.812 --> 00:03:51.731
Why do you treat
these royal lapdogs

86
00:03:51.773 --> 00:03:53.316
like they're your betters?

87
00:03:53.316 --> 00:03:54.984
They are my betters.

88
00:03:55.026 --> 00:03:56.986
You're too brazen
for your own good.

89
00:03:58.404 --> 00:04:00.907
Ser Arlan was a great knight.

90
00:04:00.949 --> 00:04:02.742
Someone will remember him.

91
00:04:02.784 --> 00:04:05.495
[fanfare playing]

92
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:09.332
Hey. Who's come?

93
00:04:09.332 --> 00:04:11.584
Can't you see the banners.
you giant cunt?

94
00:04:11.626 --> 00:04:13.753
[fanfare continues playing]

95
00:04:13.795 --> 00:04:15.672
[horses whinnying]

96
00:04:21.427 --> 00:04:24.847
Perhaps I should go back.
ser. check on the camp.

97
00:04:24.889 --> 00:04:27.058
Make sure no thieves
have been nosing about.

98
00:04:28.893 --> 00:04:30.520
Aye. I have an idea.

99
00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:32.605
Can I have your sword
to run people off with?

100
00:04:32.647 --> 00:04:34.691
-Or a mace?
-You have a knife.

101
00:04:34.732 --> 00:04:36.109
That's enough.

102
00:04:36.150 --> 00:04:38.361
You'd best be here
when I come back.

103
00:04:38.403 --> 00:04:41.406
Rob me. and I'll hunt
you down. with dogs.

104
00:04:41.447 --> 00:04:43.616
-You don't have dogs.
-I'll get some.

105
00:04:43.658 --> 00:04:44.867
Where?

106
00:04:45.702 --> 00:04:47.287
-[barks loudly]
-[gasps]

107
00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:51.082
[people chattering]

108
00:04:51.124 --> 00:04:54.127
[cheering and applause]

109
00:04:58.840 --> 00:05:00.717
[Ashford herald]
Our Lord of Ashford

110
00:05:00.758 --> 00:05:04.053
humbly welcomes
the great and honorable

111
00:05:04.095 --> 00:05:06.097
-Baelor Targaryen...
-[fanfare playing]

112
00:05:06.139 --> 00:05:08.558
...firstborn son
of King Daeron the Good.

113
00:05:10.059 --> 00:05:11.894
Prince of Dragonstone.

114
00:05:11.894 --> 00:05:13.521
Hand of the King...

115
00:05:15.273 --> 00:05:17.650
and heir to the Iron Throne.

116
00:05:17.692 --> 00:05:19.444
[horse nickering]

117
00:05:19.485 --> 00:05:21.821
Uh. and his brother.
Maekar.

118
00:05:21.863 --> 00:05:23.114
[Baelor Targaryen]
My Lord of Ashford.

119
00:05:23.156 --> 00:05:25.325
It's a great honor
to receive Your Grace.

120
00:05:25.366 --> 00:05:26.659
It's a great honor
to be received.

121
00:05:26.701 --> 00:05:28.494
My daughter. Gwin.

122
00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:36.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

123
00:05:37.587 --> 00:05:40.173
[Aerion Targaryen]
Boy. stop gaping.
See to my horse.

124
00:05:41.424 --> 00:05:43.885
[clearing throat]
I'm-- I'm not
a stable boy. m'lord.

125
00:05:45.219 --> 00:05:47.180
Not clever enough?

126
00:05:49.849 --> 00:05:52.018
-Um...
-Well. if you
can't manage horses.

127
00:05:52.060 --> 00:05:54.645
then fetch me some wine
and a pretty wench.

128
00:05:55.688 --> 00:05:57.315
Oh. m'lord pardons.

129
00:05:57.357 --> 00:05:59.776
I'm-- I'm no
serving man. either.

130
00:06:02.487 --> 00:06:04.739
I have-- I have the honor
to be a knight.

131
00:06:07.116 --> 00:06:09.285
Oh. Well...

132
00:06:10.870 --> 00:06:12.830
knighthood has fallen
on sad days.

133
00:06:14.415 --> 00:06:17.377
[horse whinnying loudly]

134
00:06:18.294 --> 00:06:20.630
-[crowd gasping]
-Whoa. whoa. Whoa. whoa.

135
00:06:20.671 --> 00:06:22.632
-[townsperson] Move away!
-Easy.

136
00:06:22.632 --> 00:06:24.467
-Easy now. come on.
-[groaning]

137
00:06:24.467 --> 00:06:27.178
Come on.
Yeah. it's okay. It's okay.

138
00:06:32.517 --> 00:06:33.893
There you are. girl.

139
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:37.146
Far too many people around.

140
00:06:37.188 --> 00:06:38.981
-[horse nickering]
-I agree. [chuckles]

141
00:06:39.023 --> 00:06:41.651
[horse master]
Where the fuck am I meant
to put all these horses?

142
00:06:41.692 --> 00:06:44.487
[Donnel of Duskendale]
The pretty ones are
always temperamental.

143
00:06:44.529 --> 00:06:47.198
Ah. she just got a bit excited.
that's all.

144
00:06:47.240 --> 00:06:49.575
[Roland Crakehall]
He meant the princeling.
not the palfrey.

145
00:06:51.744 --> 00:06:53.996
[clearing throat]
Excuse me. m'lords.

146
00:06:54.038 --> 00:06:56.749
[clearing throat]
I'm-- I'm Ser Duncan the Tall.

147
00:06:56.791 --> 00:06:58.668
Well met.
I'm Ser Roland Crakehall.

148
00:06:58.668 --> 00:07:01.045
and this is my sworn brother.
Ser Donnel of Duskendale.

149
00:07:01.087 --> 00:07:02.505
Gods. boy.

150
00:07:02.547 --> 00:07:04.590
Do you ride your horse
into battle or does it ride you?

151
00:07:04.632 --> 00:07:06.509
[Donnel]
Forgive Ser Roland.

152
00:07:06.551 --> 00:07:10.054
It's not often he must look up
to cast his eyes down.

153
00:07:10.096 --> 00:07:12.390
Yes. yes.
I'm quite the rascal.

154
00:07:12.432 --> 00:07:13.766
Now. tell me. Ser Duncan.

155
00:07:13.808 --> 00:07:15.977
is there a proper place
to shit around here?

156
00:07:16.894 --> 00:07:18.438
Uh. not really. no.

157
00:07:19.981 --> 00:07:21.065
[sighs]

158
00:07:22.567 --> 00:07:24.569
A man of such birth
has never deigned

159
00:07:24.610 --> 00:07:26.446
to disturb
his arsehole with hay.

160
00:07:26.487 --> 00:07:29.574
[scoffs] He'll deign before
the week is out. I'd wager.

161
00:07:30.867 --> 00:07:32.618
Where are you from. man?

162
00:07:32.659 --> 00:07:33.911
You don't smell House-bred.

163
00:07:35.538 --> 00:07:38.916
-No place. really.
-[chuckles] I know it.

164
00:07:38.957 --> 00:07:40.543
My family's from there.

165
00:07:40.543 --> 00:07:42.962
You're not a Darklyn
of Duskendale?

166
00:07:43.963 --> 00:07:46.048
We were crabbers
at Duskendale.

167
00:07:46.048 --> 00:07:47.758
Far back as it goes.

168
00:07:49.135 --> 00:07:50.595
[Willem Wylde]
Ser Donnel?

169
00:07:52.597 --> 00:07:55.725
May I ask. ser.
how the son of a crabber

170
00:07:55.725 --> 00:07:58.728
came to have the honor
of being a knight
in the Kingsguard?

171
00:07:59.979 --> 00:08:01.689
Same way
we became crabbers.

172
00:08:06.569 --> 00:08:07.945
"Same way we became..."

173
00:08:07.987 --> 00:08:10.114
Are you Baelor Targaryen?

174
00:08:11.157 --> 00:08:12.617
Uh. n-no.

175
00:08:12.658 --> 00:08:14.577
Then would you move
the fuck out of the way?

176
00:08:14.577 --> 00:08:16.954
Yeah. Yeah. Of course.
Apologies.

177
00:08:18.581 --> 00:08:20.332
Sorry.

178
00:08:20.374 --> 00:08:23.586
[head maid]
The princes be needing
their fucking hands washed!

179
00:08:23.586 --> 00:08:25.755
[maid]
I'm on my way. ma'am.

180
00:08:25.755 --> 00:08:28.216
[indistinct chatter]

181
00:08:30.092 --> 00:08:32.220
[head maid] Move!
A carriage is comin' through!

182
00:08:45.858 --> 00:08:47.860
[heavy door creaking open]

183
00:08:55.618 --> 00:08:58.788
[Lord Ashford]
The spring rains have swollen
many of our streams.

184
00:08:58.788 --> 00:09:00.998
Perhaps the young princes
have just been delayed?

185
00:09:01.040 --> 00:09:02.375
[Maekar Targaryen]
Fuck me.

186
00:09:02.416 --> 00:09:04.627
"Delayed."
They're not delayed.

187
00:09:04.627 --> 00:09:05.962
Do not curse
our gracious host.

188
00:09:05.962 --> 00:09:08.631
I said "fuck me."
not "fuck him."

189
00:09:08.673 --> 00:09:10.049
It's not his fault
Father bade us

190
00:09:10.091 --> 00:09:12.218
attend this
miserable circus.

191
00:09:12.260 --> 00:09:14.971
Might we discuss
this another time?

192
00:09:14.971 --> 00:09:16.556
I say we go hunting.

193
00:09:16.597 --> 00:09:18.599
Daeron has done this before.

194
00:09:19.642 --> 00:09:21.561
You should not have
commanded him
to enter the lists.

195
00:09:21.602 --> 00:09:23.229
-[person shushing]
-[Dunk gasps softly]

196
00:09:23.271 --> 00:09:24.564
[whispering]
The prince's sons
are missing.

197
00:09:25.398 --> 00:09:27.358
[Maekar]
You'd be more concerned
if it was your son. I wager.

198
00:09:27.400 --> 00:09:29.193
-Oh.
-Probably dead.

199
00:09:30.194 --> 00:09:32.655
-Dead?
-Wars have started for less.

200
00:09:32.697 --> 00:09:34.657
[liquid pouring]

201
00:09:34.657 --> 00:09:37.493
[faint chatter continues]

202
00:09:37.535 --> 00:09:39.078
[whispering]
You're big and stupid.

203
00:09:44.584 --> 00:09:46.419
[Baelor]
They have only been
missing a day.

204
00:09:47.545 --> 00:09:49.171
No doubt. Ser Roland
will turn him up

205
00:09:49.171 --> 00:09:51.007
and Aegon along with him.

206
00:09:51.007 --> 00:09:53.009
When the tourney
is over. perhaps.

207
00:09:53.009 --> 00:09:54.719
[Baelor]
Daeron belongs
on a tourney field

208
00:09:54.760 --> 00:09:57.513
no more than
Aerys or Rhaegel.

209
00:09:57.555 --> 00:10:00.016
By which you mean
he'd sooner ride a whore
than a horse.

210
00:10:00.016 --> 00:10:01.601
That is not what I said.

211
00:10:03.269 --> 00:10:05.104
[groaning]

212
00:10:05.146 --> 00:10:07.898
[Maekar]
I do not need to be reminded
of my son's failings.

213
00:10:07.940 --> 00:10:10.443
He can change.
He will change.
gods be damned.

214
00:10:10.484 --> 00:10:13.070
Or I swear.
I'll see him dead.

215
00:10:15.948 --> 00:10:17.199
You.

216
00:10:17.950 --> 00:10:19.368
Who are you?

217
00:10:19.368 --> 00:10:20.870
What do you mean
by spying on us?

218
00:10:22.872 --> 00:10:24.123
Show yourself.

219
00:10:26.459 --> 00:10:27.960
Um...
[clearing throat]

220
00:10:29.545 --> 00:10:32.381
My Lords. I do apologize
for my interruption.

221
00:10:32.423 --> 00:10:33.507
I. um...

222
00:10:36.552 --> 00:10:38.220
I have asked
Ser Manfred Dondarrion

223
00:10:38.262 --> 00:10:41.057
to vouch for me
so that I might
enter the lists.

224
00:10:41.098 --> 00:10:43.225
-but he has refused to do so.
-[Maekar] Who?

225
00:10:44.226 --> 00:10:45.394
What the fuck is going on?

226
00:10:45.436 --> 00:10:47.229
We are the intruders here.
brother.

227
00:10:47.271 --> 00:10:48.564
Come closer. ser.

228
00:10:50.316 --> 00:10:52.485
And others. too.

229
00:10:53.402 --> 00:10:57.281
You see. they say they know not
Ser Arlan of Pennytree.

230
00:10:57.323 --> 00:11:00.117
But he served them.
I swear it.

231
00:11:00.159 --> 00:11:02.078
I have his sword and shield.

232
00:11:02.078 --> 00:11:04.622
[scoffs] Sword and shield
do not make a knight.

233
00:11:04.664 --> 00:11:05.665
Mm?

234
00:11:08.876 --> 00:11:11.420
Unless you have better proof
to support what you say.

235
00:11:11.420 --> 00:11:14.048
-Some writing or--
-Do you remember him.
Your Grace?

236
00:11:16.717 --> 00:11:18.678
It was many years ago.

237
00:11:18.719 --> 00:11:20.262
You may have forgotten.

238
00:11:24.433 --> 00:11:26.018
Ser Arlan of Pennytree.

239
00:11:28.688 --> 00:11:30.439
He never won a tourney
that I know.

240
00:11:31.774 --> 00:11:33.150
But he never shamed
himself. either.

241
00:11:33.192 --> 00:11:34.819
Yes. ser.

242
00:11:34.860 --> 00:11:36.946
I mean. no.
No. he didn't.

243
00:11:36.946 --> 00:11:40.491
He overthrew Lord Stokeworth
in the melee at King's Landing

244
00:11:40.533 --> 00:11:42.827
and years before.
he unhorsed
the Grey Lion himself.

245
00:11:42.868 --> 00:11:45.162
He-- he told me of that
many a time.

246
00:11:46.872 --> 00:11:49.667
Then. you will recall
the Grey Lion's true name.

247
00:11:50.501 --> 00:11:51.752
I have no doubt.

248
00:11:52.753 --> 00:11:53.754
Um...

249
00:12:00.219 --> 00:12:02.555
Ser Damon Lannister.

250
00:12:02.596 --> 00:12:05.182
The Grey Lion.
he's Lord of Casterly Rock now.

251
00:12:05.224 --> 00:12:06.976
So he is.

252
00:12:06.976 --> 00:12:08.978
And enters the lists
upon the morrow.

253
00:12:08.978 --> 00:12:11.731
How can you possibly remember
some fucking hedge knight

254
00:12:11.772 --> 00:12:15.359
who chanced to unhorse
Damon Lannister 16 years ago?

255
00:12:15.401 --> 00:12:17.862
I make it a practice to learn
all I can of my foes.

256
00:12:17.903 --> 00:12:20.322
And why would you deign
to joust with a hedge knight?

257
00:12:20.364 --> 00:12:22.658
It was many years past.
at Storm's End.

258
00:12:22.700 --> 00:12:24.493
Lord Baratheon
held a hastilude

259
00:12:24.493 --> 00:12:26.662
to celebrate
the birth of a grandson.

260
00:12:26.662 --> 00:12:29.707
The lots made Ser Arlan
my opponent in the first tilt.

261
00:12:29.749 --> 00:12:32.334
We broke four lances
before I finally unhorsed him.

262
00:12:32.334 --> 00:12:33.544
It was seven.

263
00:12:33.586 --> 00:12:35.254
[laughing]

264
00:12:38.048 --> 00:12:39.842
I be-- believe.

265
00:12:39.842 --> 00:12:41.385
Tales grow in the telling.
I know.

266
00:12:41.427 --> 00:12:42.428
Mm.

267
00:12:43.721 --> 00:12:45.347
Do not think ill
of your old master.

268
00:12:45.389 --> 00:12:47.683
but it was four lances only.
I fear.

269
00:12:47.683 --> 00:12:49.351
As you say. Your Grace.

270
00:12:49.393 --> 00:12:51.395
I-It was four.
I do apologize.

271
00:12:51.437 --> 00:12:53.856
The old man. Ser Arlan.
he used to say

272
00:12:53.898 --> 00:12:55.441
that I was thick
as a castle wall

273
00:12:55.483 --> 00:12:56.859
and slow as an aurochs.

274
00:12:56.901 --> 00:12:58.486
No harm was done. ser.
Rise.

275
00:13:01.447 --> 00:13:03.699
You gave him back
his horse and armor

276
00:13:03.741 --> 00:13:06.118
and took no ransom.

277
00:13:06.160 --> 00:13:09.205
Ser Arlan often told me that
you were the soul of chivalry...

278
00:13:09.246 --> 00:13:10.539
-Ugh.
-...and that one day.

279
00:13:10.581 --> 00:13:13.709
the Seven Kingdoms
would be safe in your hands.

280
00:13:13.751 --> 00:13:16.086
Not for many years yet.
I pray.

281
00:13:16.128 --> 00:13:19.131
No. I-- I did not mean
that the King should--

282
00:13:19.173 --> 00:13:20.466
You wish to enter the lists.

283
00:13:20.508 --> 00:13:21.926
Is that it?

284
00:13:22.843 --> 00:13:24.261
-Yes.
-The decision rests

285
00:13:24.303 --> 00:13:25.554
with the master of the games.

286
00:13:25.596 --> 00:13:27.139
but I see no reason
to deny you.

287
00:13:27.181 --> 00:13:28.766
As you say. m'lord.

288
00:13:30.267 --> 00:13:31.310
Mm.

289
00:13:31.352 --> 00:13:33.229
[sighs]
Your Grace--

290
00:13:33.229 --> 00:13:34.897
Very well. ser.
You are grateful.

291
00:13:34.897 --> 00:13:36.315
Now. fuck off!

292
00:13:36.357 --> 00:13:38.234
You must
forgive my brother. ser.

293
00:13:38.234 --> 00:13:41.278
His sons went astray
on the way here.
and he fears for them.

294
00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:42.738
[softly] Of course.

295
00:13:42.780 --> 00:13:45.366
Um. I trust
they will not be found dead.

296
00:13:57.169 --> 00:13:58.170
[Baelor] Ser.

297
00:14:00.923 --> 00:14:02.800
You are not
of Ser Arlan's blood?

298
00:14:04.635 --> 00:14:05.845
No. I am not.

299
00:14:07.137 --> 00:14:08.764
[Baelor]
By law. only a trueborn son

300
00:14:08.764 --> 00:14:10.474
is entitled to inherit
a knight's arms.

301
00:14:10.516 --> 00:14:12.810
You must needs find
a new device. ser.

302
00:14:13.602 --> 00:14:14.937
A sigil of your own.

303
00:14:16.647 --> 00:14:17.648
I will.

304
00:14:19.567 --> 00:14:21.235
Thank you again.
Your Grace.

305
00:14:23.237 --> 00:14:26.282
I will fight bravely.
You'll see.

306
00:14:32.746 --> 00:14:33.831
It's this way.

307
00:14:33.873 --> 00:14:35.207
[puppeteer]
You are no knight.

308
00:14:36.165 --> 00:14:38.294
-[grunting]
-[crowd groaning]

309
00:14:39.503 --> 00:14:40.504
[crowd exclaiming]

310
00:14:40.546 --> 00:14:42.673
You are Florian the Fool.

311
00:14:42.715 --> 00:14:44.758
-I am. my lady.
-[crowd gasping]

312
00:14:46.135 --> 00:14:48.053
As great a fool
as ever lived.

313
00:14:48.095 --> 00:14:50.264
[crowd jeering]

314
00:14:51.765 --> 00:14:54.518
And as great a knight
as well!

315
00:14:54.560 --> 00:14:56.395
[cheering and applause]

316
00:14:59.231 --> 00:15:01.400
A fool and a knight.

317
00:15:02.318 --> 00:15:04.737
I have never heard
of such a thing.

318
00:15:04.778 --> 00:15:06.572
[Florian the Fool]
Sweet lady.

319
00:15:06.614 --> 00:15:10.326
All men are fools.
and all men are knights...

320
00:15:10.326 --> 00:15:11.660
[whispering]
...where women are concerned.

321
00:15:11.702 --> 00:15:14.163
[laughter]

322
00:15:14.163 --> 00:15:16.498
[cheering and applause]

323
00:15:16.498 --> 00:15:18.500
[violin playing]

324
00:15:25.257 --> 00:15:26.508
[Dunk]
Hello there.

325
00:15:27.635 --> 00:15:28.761
[coin jingles]

326
00:15:28.802 --> 00:15:30.888
And. uh. one for last night.

327
00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:33.015
-[both chuckle softly]
-[Egg] That was great.

328
00:15:33.057 --> 00:15:35.267
How'd you do the fire tricks?

329
00:15:35.309 --> 00:15:36.644
Oh.

330
00:15:40.189 --> 00:15:42.775
[gasps] Is it pollen?

331
00:15:42.816 --> 00:15:45.361
Yeah. we. uh.
we collect it on the way.

332
00:15:48.822 --> 00:15:50.908
[Egg] I've never seen
such giant puppets.

333
00:15:50.950 --> 00:15:52.242
Do you make them yourself?

334
00:15:52.284 --> 00:15:55.329
My uncle builds them.
but I paint.

335
00:15:56.413 --> 00:15:57.998
Could you paint
something for me?

336
00:15:58.999 --> 00:16:00.918
Uh. I-- I have the coin to pay.

337
00:16:00.960 --> 00:16:02.753
I. um... just...

338
00:16:03.754 --> 00:16:07.216
[chuckles] Um. I need to paint
something over the chalice.

339
00:16:07.257 --> 00:16:09.927
Well. what would you want?

340
00:16:11.345 --> 00:16:12.888
Um...

341
00:16:12.888 --> 00:16:14.807
[clicking tongue]
I... [sighs]

342
00:16:14.848 --> 00:16:17.267
I don't-- I don't actually know.
[chuckles]

343
00:16:17.309 --> 00:16:18.310
I. uh...

344
00:16:19.478 --> 00:16:21.730
Sorry. you must think me
a fool. [chuckles]

345
00:16:21.730 --> 00:16:24.358
All men are fools.
and all men are knights.

346
00:16:26.318 --> 00:16:27.319
Mm.

347
00:16:30.823 --> 00:16:31.824
Um...

348
00:16:32.908 --> 00:16:34.618
Yeah.
[clearing throat]

349
00:16:36.078 --> 00:16:38.414
The-- the gray is a bit drab.

350
00:16:38.455 --> 00:16:39.873
Aye. um...

351
00:16:40.958 --> 00:16:44.086
Yeah. the--
the field should be
the color of sunset

352
00:16:44.920 --> 00:16:47.464
'cause the old man always
liked sunsets and. uh--

353
00:16:47.506 --> 00:16:49.758
An elm tree.
A big one.

354
00:16:49.758 --> 00:16:52.511
Like the one by the river
with the brown trunk

355
00:16:52.553 --> 00:16:54.972
and the green branches.

356
00:16:55.014 --> 00:16:57.975
Aye.
An elm tree.
that would serve.

357
00:16:58.976 --> 00:17:00.894
But with
a shooting star above.

358
00:17:01.895 --> 00:17:03.939
-Could you do that?
-Mm-hmm.

359
00:17:05.482 --> 00:17:08.777
Thank you. um.
I'm-- I'm Ser Duncan the Tall.

360
00:17:08.777 --> 00:17:10.445
[laughing]

361
00:17:10.445 --> 00:17:12.531
Um. I'm Tanselle.

362
00:17:12.573 --> 00:17:15.951
The-- the boys used to call me
Tanselle Too-Tall.

363
00:17:15.951 --> 00:17:17.286
[chuckles]

364
00:17:17.327 --> 00:17:19.663
You're not too tall.
I mean. you're just right for...

365
00:17:20.580 --> 00:17:21.665
Uh...

366
00:17:22.624 --> 00:17:24.501
For?

367
00:17:24.542 --> 00:17:26.211
Puppets.

368
00:17:27.421 --> 00:17:28.964
Yeah. puppets. [chuckles]

369
00:17:29.006 --> 00:17:31.300
[sighs]
Okay. I'll. um...

370
00:17:31.341 --> 00:17:33.343
-Wait. The shield.
-Yes. sorry.

371
00:17:33.385 --> 00:17:34.553
-Yes. the shield.
-Yeah.

372
00:17:34.595 --> 00:17:36.513
Was that ill-handled?

373
00:17:36.555 --> 00:17:39.099
-Hm?
-The-- the puppet girl.

374
00:17:40.225 --> 00:17:41.226
Oh.

375
00:17:42.686 --> 00:17:45.314
It-- it just-- it didn't feel
well-handled.

376
00:17:46.565 --> 00:17:48.484
She is painting
your shield.

377
00:17:48.525 --> 00:17:49.902
Yeah. for pay.

378
00:17:49.943 --> 00:17:52.237
[townsperson shouting]

379
00:17:52.279 --> 00:17:54.156
You are both gigantic.

380
00:17:55.991 --> 00:17:58.827
[crowd shouting]

381
00:17:58.827 --> 00:18:00.245
Is that promising?

382
00:18:01.413 --> 00:18:02.623
It's a...

383
00:18:04.208 --> 00:18:05.584
commonality.

384
00:18:07.169 --> 00:18:09.755
Right. yeah. [clearing throat]
C-Commonality.

385
00:18:11.298 --> 00:18:12.382
[townsperson]
I don't know.

386
00:18:12.424 --> 00:18:14.426
[indistinct chatter]

387
00:18:18.055 --> 00:18:19.765
Do you think I'll ever make
a knight one day?

388
00:18:20.682 --> 00:18:22.851
Sure. why not?
You're a likely lad.

389
00:18:22.893 --> 00:18:24.937
-I'm a bit puny.
-[chuckles]

390
00:18:24.978 --> 00:18:27.356
-You'll grow.
-Even for my age.

391
00:18:27.397 --> 00:18:29.024
Everyone's always told me so.

392
00:18:32.611 --> 00:18:34.863
Everyone's always told me
I was stupid.

393
00:18:43.872 --> 00:18:44.873
And?

394
00:18:45.916 --> 00:18:47.000
Hm?

395
00:18:47.960 --> 00:18:49.503
-Hm? What?
-What?

396
00:18:50.796 --> 00:18:53.674
What did you do when people
said you were stupid. ser?

397
00:18:55.217 --> 00:18:57.386
What business
is that of yours?

398
00:18:57.427 --> 00:18:59.221
My problems are my own.

399
00:18:59.221 --> 00:19:02.224
I thought...
Aren't you trying to help me?

400
00:19:02.266 --> 00:19:04.393
Help you what? Grow?

401
00:19:04.393 --> 00:19:05.769
Yes!
Hedge knight. you.

402
00:19:08.438 --> 00:19:10.774
What is this piss froth?
I need muscle.

403
00:19:11.817 --> 00:19:13.861
Will you heed my call to war?

404
00:19:14.903 --> 00:19:16.280
Aha! Good.

405
00:19:16.321 --> 00:19:17.781
Go! Get up. come.

406
00:19:17.823 --> 00:19:20.075
-[crowd exclaiming]
-Ready!

407
00:19:22.077 --> 00:19:23.412
Hey!

408
00:19:23.412 --> 00:19:25.289
Dry those palms.
you clam-handed cunt.

409
00:19:25.330 --> 00:19:27.457
We're not in your sister's
chambers now.

410
00:19:27.499 --> 00:19:29.168
-Ready?
-[spitting]

411
00:19:29.209 --> 00:19:31.336
[crowd continues shouting]

412
00:19:31.378 --> 00:19:33.881
-Go!
-Pull!

413
00:19:34.631 --> 00:19:37.509
If we lose this.
I'll be drowning your firstborn!

414
00:19:37.551 --> 00:19:39.303
-Come on!
-Pull! Pull!

415
00:19:39.344 --> 00:19:41.763
Pull. you cunt-strapped
dandelions!

416
00:19:41.805 --> 00:19:44.808
[♪ dramatic string music
playing]

417
00:19:50.689 --> 00:19:52.691
I'll be back. I'll be back!
I'll be back.

418
00:19:52.733 --> 00:19:54.484
Lyonel!
What are you doing?

419
00:19:54.526 --> 00:19:56.403
-I'm thirsty.
-Lyonel!

420
00:19:57.988 --> 00:19:59.990
-Pull!
-[Egg shouting]

421
00:20:01.783 --> 00:20:03.285
I'm thirsty. cunt.

422
00:20:03.285 --> 00:20:05.829
[crowd continues shouting]

423
00:20:05.871 --> 00:20:07.831
-I'm thirsty!
-[Dunk shouting]

424
00:20:11.668 --> 00:20:12.753
[smacking]
Looking good.

425
00:20:14.588 --> 00:20:16.590
[grunting]

426
00:20:20.093 --> 00:20:22.888
Fucking pull!

427
00:20:25.057 --> 00:20:27.476
[crowd roaring]

428
00:20:29.561 --> 00:20:31.396
[crowd exclaiming]

429
00:20:32.773 --> 00:20:34.775
[joyful chatter]

430
00:20:47.079 --> 00:20:49.081
[faint cheering]

431
00:20:51.750 --> 00:20:54.127
-You do good work.
-None better.

432
00:20:56.797 --> 00:20:58.382
I need some armor
on the morrow.

433
00:20:59.800 --> 00:21:02.886
Gorget. greaves.
and great helm.

434
00:21:02.928 --> 00:21:04.388
Are you jousting
or working?

435
00:21:05.514 --> 00:21:06.598
Both. perhaps.

436
00:21:10.477 --> 00:21:13.438
You're a big one.
though I've armored bigger.

437
00:21:17.484 --> 00:21:20.445
I have some pieces
in the wagon that might do.

438
00:21:20.487 --> 00:21:23.740
Nothing prettied up
with gold or silver. like.

439
00:21:23.782 --> 00:21:27.035
Just good steel.
strong and plain.

440
00:21:27.035 --> 00:21:28.912
I make helms
that look like helms.

441
00:21:28.954 --> 00:21:31.623
not winged pigs
and fancy foreign fruit.

442
00:21:33.417 --> 00:21:36.378
But mine'll serve you better
if you take a lance in the face.

443
00:21:36.378 --> 00:21:39.381
That's all I want.
How much?

444
00:21:39.423 --> 00:21:42.426
Eight hundred stag.
for I'm feeling kindly.

445
00:21:42.467 --> 00:21:43.927
Eight hundred?

446
00:21:45.846 --> 00:21:48.390
Perhaps I could trade you some
armor made for a smaller man.

447
00:21:48.390 --> 00:21:50.726
A half helm.
a mail hauberk.

448
00:21:50.726 --> 00:21:53.812
Steely Pate sells
only his own work.

449
00:22:07.117 --> 00:22:09.870
[sighs]
I could make use of the metal.

450
00:22:10.912 --> 00:22:12.664
If it's not too rusted.
I'll take it

451
00:22:12.706 --> 00:22:14.374
and armor you for...

452
00:22:16.043 --> 00:22:17.294
600.

453
00:22:18.920 --> 00:22:21.173
I only have two stags.

454
00:22:21.214 --> 00:22:23.050
[Steely Pate]
Buys you a day.

455
00:22:26.720 --> 00:22:28.263
Send your squire
along with the rest.

456
00:22:28.305 --> 00:22:30.515
or else I'll sell me wares
to the next man.

457
00:22:31.892 --> 00:22:33.602
You'll get it all back.
I swear it.

458
00:22:34.811 --> 00:22:36.521
I mean to be
a champion here.

459
00:22:36.563 --> 00:22:37.773
Do you. now?

460
00:22:39.691 --> 00:22:41.610
And the others
all came just...

461
00:22:42.611 --> 00:22:43.862
just to cheer you on?

462
00:22:48.075 --> 00:22:49.868
[horse nickering]

463
00:22:49.910 --> 00:22:52.913
[♪ gentle music playing]

464
00:23:03.048 --> 00:23:05.675
Is there any measure of a fool
I fail to meet?

465
00:23:12.182 --> 00:23:16.228
If I win. I'll come back
and buy you again.

466
00:23:16.269 --> 00:23:17.604
-I promise.
-[chortling]

467
00:23:20.857 --> 00:23:22.901
Best girl.

468
00:23:22.943 --> 00:23:24.820
[nickering]

469
00:23:24.820 --> 00:23:27.823
[♪ gentle music
continues playing]

470
00:23:32.452 --> 00:23:33.870
[coins jingling]

471
00:23:40.293 --> 00:23:41.628
That's for her.

472
00:23:44.005 --> 00:23:46.133
See she has some
oats tonight. yeah?

473
00:23:54.307 --> 00:23:55.767
And an apple. too.

474
00:24:05.944 --> 00:24:08.196
[crowd chattering]

475
00:24:08.196 --> 00:24:09.948
[Dunk]
No turning back now.
I suppose.

476
00:24:12.492 --> 00:24:13.785
[grunting softly]

477
00:24:17.956 --> 00:24:20.542
You know. the old man
lived nigh on 60 years

478
00:24:20.542 --> 00:24:23.044
-and was never a champion.
-There's a bug in my cider.

479
00:24:24.671 --> 00:24:27.716
If I could call myself
a champion of Ashford Meadow...

480
00:24:28.925 --> 00:24:30.510
even for an hour...

481
00:24:32.137 --> 00:24:35.140
maybe some great house
might take me into its service.

482
00:24:37.184 --> 00:24:39.227
Perhaps even
House Targaryen.

483
00:24:41.062 --> 00:24:43.899
You suppose the dragon house
employs many hedge knights. ser?

484
00:24:44.816 --> 00:24:46.818
Enough of that.

485
00:24:46.860 --> 00:24:49.070
I'll have you know
Ser Donnel of the Kingsguard

486
00:24:49.070 --> 00:24:50.864
is but the son of a crabber.

487
00:24:52.032 --> 00:24:53.658
Ser Donnel?

488
00:24:53.700 --> 00:24:55.660
-Of Duskendale?
-Yeah.

489
00:24:55.702 --> 00:24:58.538
His father owns half
the crabbing fleets in Westeros.

490
00:24:59.748 --> 00:25:00.832
What?!

491
00:25:02.918 --> 00:25:04.211
How would you know?

492
00:25:05.045 --> 00:25:06.796
I like fishing.

493
00:25:07.714 --> 00:25:08.840
[raucous laughter]

494
00:25:08.882 --> 00:25:10.592
[loud horn blowing]

495
00:25:10.592 --> 00:25:12.010
[people cheering]

496
00:25:12.052 --> 00:25:13.553
It's time!

497
00:25:14.888 --> 00:25:16.097
Right. come on. let's go.

498
00:25:16.139 --> 00:25:18.225
Come on. pick your feet up.
Let's go.

499
00:25:19.226 --> 00:25:21.228
[horn blowing]

500
00:25:23.313 --> 00:25:24.731
[Egg]
Wait for me!

501
00:25:28.777 --> 00:25:31.780
[horns continue blowing]

502
00:25:33.281 --> 00:25:34.824
[Egg] Ser Duncan!

503
00:25:34.866 --> 00:25:36.076
Ser Duncan!

504
00:25:37.827 --> 00:25:39.621
-[Dunk] Oh.
-[Egg grunting]

505
00:25:39.621 --> 00:25:41.289
-[Dunk] You alright?
-[Egg] Yeah.

506
00:25:41.289 --> 00:25:43.291
[crowd clamoring]

507
00:25:54.719 --> 00:25:57.305
-[crowd continues shouting]
-[horse whinnying]

508
00:25:59.599 --> 00:26:01.601
[crowd cheering]

509
00:26:09.943 --> 00:26:11.027
[jouster laughing]

510
00:26:15.865 --> 00:26:17.993
-[jouster exclaiming]
-[crowd cheering]

511
00:26:18.034 --> 00:26:21.121
For the new gods
and old!

512
00:26:22.956 --> 00:26:24.958
[crowd cheering]

513
00:26:34.050 --> 00:26:37.053
-Lance!
-[people shouting indistinctly]

514
00:26:38.805 --> 00:26:41.182
Shield. and lance.

515
00:26:42.225 --> 00:26:44.227
[horse whinnying]

516
00:26:47.897 --> 00:26:48.898
Helmet!

517
00:26:50.775 --> 00:26:52.902
Hey. who's that?

518
00:26:52.944 --> 00:26:55.488
Prince Valarr.
Baelor's son.

519
00:26:56.615 --> 00:26:58.366
-Second in line to the throne.
-[Valarr] Shield!

520
00:26:58.408 --> 00:27:00.285
He's the favorite.
I'd wager.

521
00:27:00.327 --> 00:27:01.870
I'll take that bet. ser.

522
00:27:05.206 --> 00:27:07.208
[crowd calming]

523
00:27:09.461 --> 00:27:11.463
[horse neighing]

524
00:27:14.341 --> 00:27:16.259
[horse whinnying.
stomping]

525
00:27:20.472 --> 00:27:23.433
Lord Ashford fucks his sheep!

526
00:27:23.475 --> 00:27:26.144
[laughter]

527
00:27:26.186 --> 00:27:27.937
[horn blowing]

528
00:27:27.979 --> 00:27:28.980
[horse whinnying]

529
00:27:30.398 --> 00:27:31.858
[shouting]

530
00:27:35.445 --> 00:27:36.488
[jouster shouting]

531
00:27:36.529 --> 00:27:39.532
[♪ tense music playing]

532
00:27:41.618 --> 00:27:43.662
[crowd roaring]

533
00:27:43.703 --> 00:27:46.122
Come on! Whoo!

534
00:27:46.164 --> 00:27:48.416
[crowd continues cheering]

535
00:27:48.416 --> 00:27:50.418
[horn blowing]

536
00:27:51.795 --> 00:27:54.130
[Leo Tyrell] Squire!
Lance. lance. lance!

537
00:27:54.172 --> 00:27:57.175
[overlapping shouting]

538
00:27:59.344 --> 00:28:02.347
-[horse whinnying]
-[shouting continues]

539
00:28:07.769 --> 00:28:09.646
-[crashing]
-[crowd cheering]

540
00:28:10.605 --> 00:28:12.607
Ser.
Put me down. ser.

541
00:28:14.442 --> 00:28:16.444
[cheering continues]

542
00:28:22.617 --> 00:28:23.910
Hyah! Hyah!

543
00:28:29.374 --> 00:28:31.126
[horse neighing. whinnying]

544
00:28:35.880 --> 00:28:36.923
-Whoa!
-Whoa!

545
00:28:45.974 --> 00:28:48.476
[jousters shouting]

546
00:28:48.518 --> 00:28:50.645
-[horse whinnying]
-[Dunk exhales sharply]

547
00:28:53.106 --> 00:28:55.108
[noises muffling]

548
00:28:56.192 --> 00:28:57.277
[muffled shouting]

549
00:29:01.906 --> 00:29:03.908
[breathing heavily]

550
00:29:07.871 --> 00:29:09.330
Die!

551
00:29:09.372 --> 00:29:12.000
Do you yield.
Blackfyre bastards?!

552
00:29:12.000 --> 00:29:13.668
[exclaiming]

553
00:29:13.710 --> 00:29:15.712
[blade scraping]

554
00:29:17.422 --> 00:29:19.007
Splendid riding tonight.

555
00:29:21.885 --> 00:29:24.220
Mm. the part with the fish
was disgusting.

556
00:29:30.602 --> 00:29:32.771
Something the matter. ser?

557
00:29:32.812 --> 00:29:34.689
[blade continues scraping]

558
00:29:36.399 --> 00:29:39.027
Do great knights
live in the hedges

559
00:29:39.068 --> 00:29:42.030
and die by the side
of a muddy road?

560
00:29:42.071 --> 00:29:43.198
[scoffs]

561
00:29:46.367 --> 00:29:47.660
I think not.

562
00:29:51.539 --> 00:29:54.375
Ser Arlan wasn't gifted
with sword or lance.

563
00:29:54.375 --> 00:29:57.712
and he drank.
and he whored.

564
00:29:57.712 --> 00:30:00.131
and he was a hard man
to know.

565
00:30:03.676 --> 00:30:05.220
He made no friends. either.

566
00:30:06.262 --> 00:30:09.307
He lived nigh on 60 years
and never was a champion.

567
00:30:10.850 --> 00:30:13.728
Mm. what chance do I have?
Truly?

568
00:30:14.938 --> 00:30:16.439
[sighs]

569
00:30:17.273 --> 00:30:18.608
But he was good to me.

570
00:30:24.405 --> 00:30:25.990
I wasn't his family...

571
00:30:27.283 --> 00:30:28.910
but he kept me
like we were.

572
00:30:33.873 --> 00:30:35.917
He raised me to be
an honorable man.

573
00:30:39.754 --> 00:30:44.008
And all these noble lords

574
00:30:44.050 --> 00:30:46.010
can't even
remember his name.

575
00:30:49.097 --> 00:30:51.307
His name was
Ser Arlan of Pennytree.

576
00:30:53.184 --> 00:30:54.811
And I am his legacy.

577
00:30:56.104 --> 00:30:57.730
On the morrow...

578
00:30:59.482 --> 00:31:01.526
we will show them
what his hand has wrought.

579
00:31:02.652 --> 00:31:05.655
[♪ somber music playing]

580
00:31:09.367 --> 00:31:12.370
[♪ dramatic music playing]

581
00:31:13.305 --> 00:32:13.341
